# The number of ways you can split a pie among 5 people
# is equivalent to 5 ways to split it to an individual.
#
# For example: I will give you 4 ways to split a pie among 3 people:
# 1. a) split the pie evenly. If we split the pie
# into three equal parts, then the 3rd part becomes a fourth
# because it has been split already. So, if I have one pie to eat and decide to
# use 1/3rd, I will inevitably spend most of my time waiting. The same applies
# to 1 part, 2 parts, etc. For example: if one person wants to eat two thirds
# of the pie, it takes two times longer because you end up waiting for the whole pie
# to be served. This is the most straightforward way and can only work for one, not many.
# So, this is not a good solution for the original question. This is important
# as we will be using similar arguments later that will make sense at that time.
# 2. b) Split pie unevenly. If we choose a way to split, say into two, one
# will have 1/2 of pie and the other person will have 1/4 of a piece. But 
# what if one person wants more? So, by splitting unequally,
# we are splitting it in a way that is not always possible.
# 3. c) Order the pie first (or have two more pieces). Then split the 
# pie between two people that share the same preference and split the other
# pie among the remaining.
# 4. d) The above example makes you realize that it is better to have equal
# sized pieces of pie rather than unequal. So, we simply slice the pie
# into 6 equal pieces and assign one piece to each person. This is the 
# simplest solution to the original question.

# Note that if we were to find the minimum possible number of ways to split
# an eight-person pie, that would also be 6 because we have 8 people with a single
# pie. But in this case we do not know the number of people in advance
# and therefore we must compute the value as we proceed to solve the

This problem was asked in Amazon and Expedia.

We first allocate 1000000 of memory and then run a loop 1000 times to print int x and increment it by 2 each time.
So, after we have exited the loop, the int variable x should be allocated 10 lakh (10,000,000) spaces,
and after which it tries to decrement the variable by 1 using – operator. 
This results in 10lakh spaces still being allocated and we have created a leak in memory.

The solution would be to use - or – in place of – operator
